title: Age structure in Ethiopia 2018
summary: This is a multi-line chart with 3 lines representing 0-14 years, 15-64 years, and 65 years and older. The y axis denotes Share of total population and the x axis denotes Year.
Overall 15-64 years is gradually increasing, 0-14 years is gradually decreasing, 65 years and older is roughly constant,  throughout the Year
The lines ordered according to average values of Share of total population in descending order is: 1. 15-64 years, 2. 0-14 years, and lastly, 3. 65 years and older.
Throughout the period, 15-64 years generally had the highest Share of total population relative to others with an average of 53.32, and it reached its maximum at 2018 with a value of 55.72.
Followed by 0-14 years which ranks as the second topmpost line , with an average of 43.3 Share of total population,reaching its highest point  at 2008 with a value of 45.7.
65 years and older mostly had the least Share of total population with a mean value of 3.38, which peaked at 2018 with a value of 3.5.
